other_tests.findings: Panhypopituitarism but detectable levels of the pituitary hormones.
Hypernatremia and polyuria; elevated plasma osmolality and low urinary osmolality confirmed diabetes insipidus.
True anophthalmia, no sella turcica, presence of a pituitary stalk but no visualization of anterior and posterior pituitary glands, and complete bilateral cleft palate.
